  "answer": {
    "role": "assistant",
    "content": "<html>\n<head>\n    <title>P vs NP Interactive Explorer</title>\n    <style>\n        body {\n            font-family: Arial, sans-serif;\n            max-width: 900px;\n            margin: 0 auto;\n            padding: 20px;\n            line-height: 1.6;\n        }\n        .panel {\n            border: 1px solid #ccc;\n            padding: 15px;\n            margin-bottom: 20px;\n        }\n        button, select, input {\n            margin: 5px;\n            padding: 5px;\n        }\n        .problem-instance {\n            font-family: monospace;\n            white-space: pre;\n        }\n        .hidden {\n            display: none;\n        }\n        table {\n            border-collapse: collapse;\n            width: 100%;\n        }\n        td, th {\n            border: 1px solid #ddd;\n            padding: 8px;\n            text-align: left;\n        }\n    </style>\n</head>\n<body>\n    <h1>P vs NP Interactive Explorer</h1>\n    \n    <div class=\"panel\">\n        <h2>Concept Overview</h2>\n        <p>\n            <strong>P problems</strong> are those that can be solved quickly (in polynomial time) by a computer.\n            <br>\n            <strong>NP problems</strong> are those whose solutions can be verified quickly, but may not be solvable quickly.\n        </p>\n        <p>The P vs NP question asks: Are all problems with easily verifiable solutions also easily solvable?</p>\n        \n        <div>\n            <button id=\"showPExamples\">Show P Problem Examples</button>\n            <button id=\"showNPExamples\">Show NP Problem Examples</button>\n            <button id=\"showNPComplete\">Show NP-Complete Problems</button>\n        </div>\n        \n        <div id=\"examplesContainer\" class=\"hidden\">\n            <h3 id=\"examplesTitle\"></h3>\n            <ul id=\"examplesList\"></ul>\n        </div>\n    </div>\n    \n    <div class=\"panel\">\n        <h2>Problem Complexity Simulator</h2>\n        <p>Compare how problem complexity grows with input size:</p>\n        \n        <div>\n            <label>Problem Type:\n                <select id=\"problemType\">\n                    <option value=\"p\">P Problem (e.g., Sorting)</option>\n                    <option value=\"np\">NP Problem (e.g., Traveling Salesman)</option>\n                    <option value=\"exp\">Exponential Problem</option>\n                </select>\n            </label>\n            \n            <label>Input Size (n): <input type=\"range\" id=\"inputSize\" min=\"1\" max=\"20\" value=\"5\"></label>\n            <span id=\"currentSize\">5</span>\n        </div>\n        \n        <div>\n            <button id=\"calculateComplexity\">Calculate Complexity</button>\n        </div>\n        \n        <div id=\"complexityResults\" class=\"hidden\">\n            <h3>Complexity Analysis</h3>\n            <p>\n                For n = <span id=\"resultN\"></span>:\n                <br>\n                Time complexity: O(<span id=\"timeComplexity\"></span>) = <span id=\"timeValue\"></span> operations\n            </p>\n            <div id=\"graphContainer\" style=\"height: 200px; border: 1px solid #000; position: relative;\">\n                <!-- Graph will be drawn here -->\n            </div>\n        </div>\n    </div>\n    \n    <div class=\"panel\">\n        <h2>Problem Solver</h2>\n        <p>Try solving different types of problems:</p>\n        \n        <div>\n            <label>Select Problem:\n                <select id=\"problemSelector\">\n                    <option value=\"sort\">Sorting (P)</option>\n                    <option value=\"tsp\">Traveling Salesman (NP)</option>\n                    <option value=\"sat\">Boolean Satisfiability (NP-Complete)</option>\n                </select>\n            </label>\n        </div>\n        \n        <div id=\"problemInputContainer\">\n            <!-- Problem-specific input will go here -->\n        </div>\n        \n        <div>\n            <button id=\"solveProblem\">Solve Problem</button>\n            <button id=\"verifySolution\" disabled>Verify Solution</button>\n        </div>\n        \n        <div id=\"solutionContainer\" class=\"hidden\">\n            <h3>Solution</h3>\n            <div id=\"solutionOutput\"></div>\n            <div id=\"verificationResult\"></div>\n        </div>\n    </div>\n    \n    <div class=\"panel\">\n        <h2>P vs NP Implications</h2>\n        <p>Explore what P = NP would mean:</p>\n        \n        <div>\n            <button id=\"showImplications\">Show Implications</button>\n            <button id=\"showCurrentStatus\">Show Current Status</button>\n        </div>\n        \n        <div id=\"implicationsContent\" class=\"hidden\">\n            <h3>If P = NP:</h3>\n            <ul id=\"implicationsList\"></ul>\n            \n            <h3>Current Status:</h3>\n            <p id=\"statusText\"></p>\n        </div>\n    </div>\n    \n    <div class=\"panel\">\n        <h2>Advanced Exploration</h2>\n        <p>Deeper technical concepts:</p>\n        \n        <div>\n            <button id=\"showReductions\">Show Problem Reductions</button>\n            <button id=\"showAlgorithms\">Compare Algorithms</button>\n        </div>\n        \n        <div id=\"advancedContent\" class=\"hidden\">\n            <h3 id=\"advancedTitle\"></h3>\n            <div id=\"advancedText\"></div>\n        </div>\n    </div>\n\n    <script>\n        // Problem examples data\n        const examples = {\n            p: [\n                \"Sorting a list of numbers\",\n                \"Finding the shortest path between two points (Dijkstra's algorithm)\",\n                \"Determining if a number is prime (AKS primality test)\",\n                \"Matrix multiplication\"\n            ],\n            np: [\n                \"Traveling Salesman Problem (find shortest route visiting all cities)\",\n                \"Boolean satisfiability problem (SAT)\",\n                \"Graph coloring\",\n                \"Subset sum problem\"\n            ],\n            npComplete: [\n                \"All NP-complete problems are in NP and as hard as any problem in NP\",\n                \"SAT was the first problem proven to be NP-complete (Cook-Levin theorem)\",\n                \"Other NP-complete problems can be reduced to SAT\",\n                \"Includes: Knapsack problem, Hamiltonian path, 3-coloring\"\n            ]\n        };\n        \n        // Complexity functions\n        const complexityFunctions = {\n            p: n => n * Math.log2(n),\n            np: n => Math.pow(2, n),\n            exp: n => Math.pow(n, n)\n        };\n        \n        // Problem generators and solvers\n        const problemHandlers = {\n            sort: {\n                generate: n => {\n                    const nums = [];\n                    for (let i = 0; i < n; i++) {\n                        nums.push(Math.floor(Math.random() * 100));\n                    }\n                    return nums.join(\", \");\n                },\n                solve: input => {\n                    return input.split(\", \").map(Number).sort((a, b) => a - b).join(\", \");\n                },\n                verify: (input, solution) => {\n                    const sorted = input.split(\", \").map(Number).sort((a, b) => a - b).join(\", \");\n                    return solution === sorted;\n                }\n            },\n            tsp: {\n                generate: n => {\n                    const cities = [];\n                    for (let i = 0; i < n; i++) {\n                        cities.push(`City ${String.fromCharCode(65 + i)}`);\n                    }\n                    return cities.join(\" → \");\n                },\n                solve: input => {\n                    // \"Solve\" by just shuffling - in reality this would be much more complex\n                    const cities = input.split(\" → \");\n                    for (let i = cities.length - 1; i > 0; i--) {\n                        const j = Math.floor(Math.random() * (i + 1));\n                        [cities[i], cities[j]] = [cities[j], cities[i]];\n                    }\n                    return cities.join(\" → \");\n                },\n                verify: (input, solution) => {\n                    const inputCities = input.split(\" → \");\n                    const solutionCities = solution.split(\" → \");\n                    \n                    // Check all cities are present\n                    if (inputCities.length !== solutionCities.length) return false;\n                    for (const city of inputCities) {\n                        if (!solutionCities.includes(city)) return false;\n                    }\n                    \n                    return true; // In reality we'd check for shortest path\n                }\n            },\n            sat: {\n                generate: n => {\n                    const vars = [];\n                    for (let i = 0; i < n; i++) {\n                        vars.push(String.fromCharCode(65 + i));\n                    }\n                    \n                    const clauses = [];\n                    for (let i = 0; i < n; i++) {\n                        const clause = [];\n                        for (let j = 0; j < 3; j++) {\n                            const varIndex = Math.floor(Math.random() * n);\n                            const negate = Math.random() > 0.5;\n                            clause.push((negate ? \"¬\" : \"\") + vars[varIndex]);\n                        }\n                        clauses.push(\"(\" + clause.join(\" ∨ \") + \")\");\n                    }\n                    \n                    return clauses.join(\" ∧ \");\n                },\n                solve: input => {\n                    // \"Solve\" by random assignment - in reality this would be much more complex\n                    const vars = new Set();\n                    const matches = input.matchAll(/[A-Z]/g);\n                    for (const match of matches) {\n                        vars.add(match[0]);\n                    }\n                    \n                    const assignment = {};\n                    for (const v of vars) {\n                        assignment[v] = Math.random() > 0.5;\n                    }\n                    \n                    return Object.entries(assignment).map(([v, val]) => `${v}=${val}`).join(\", \");\n                },\n                verify: (input, solution) => {\n                    // Parse assignment\n                    const assignment = {};\n                    const assignments = solution.split(\", \");\n                    for (const a of assignments) {\n                        const [v, val] = a.split(\"=\");\n                        assignment[v] = val === \"true\";\n                    }\n                    \n                    // Evaluate each clause\n                    const clauses = input.split(\" ∧ \");\n                    for (const clause of clauses) {\n                        const literals = clause.slice(1, -1).split(\" ∨ \");\n                        let clauseSatisfied = false;\n                        \n                        for (const lit of literals) {\n                            let varName, value;\n                            if (lit.startsWith(\"¬\")) {\n                                varName = lit.slice(1);\n                                value = !assignment[varName];\n                            } else {\n                                varName = lit;\n                                value = assignment[varName];\n                            }\n                            \n                            if (value) {\n                                clauseSatisfied = true;\n                                break;\n                            }\n                        }\n                        \n                        if (!clauseSatisfied) return false;\n                    }\n                    \n                    return true;\n                }\n            }\n        };\n        \n        // Implications data\n        const implications = [\n            \"Many important optimization problems would become tractable\",\n            \"Cryptography as we know it would be broken (most encryption schemes rely on P ≠ NP)\",\n            \"Mathematical proofs could be automated (given a good enough verifier)\",\n            \"Protein folding and other complex scientific problems could be solved efficiently\",\n            \"AI could potentially be much more powerful\"\n        ];\n        \n        const currentStatus = [\n            \"Most computer scientists believe P ≠ NP\",\n            \"No proof has been found either way\",\n            \"The Clay Mathematics Institute offers $1 million for a proof\",\n            \"Many approaches have been tried (circuit complexity, descriptive complexity, etc.)\",\n            \"Some researchers have claimed proofs, but none have been widely accepted\"\n        ];\n        \n        // Advanced content\n        const advancedContent = {\n            reductions: {\n                title: \"Problem Reductions\",\n                content: `\n                    <p>Reductions are key to understanding NP-completeness. A problem A can be reduced to problem B if we can convert instances of A to instances of B.</p>\n                    <p>If A reduces to B and B is in P, then A is in P.</p>\n                    <p>NP-complete problems are those to which any NP problem can be reduced.</p>\n                    <p>Example reductions:</p>\n                    <ul>\n                        <li>3SAT → Independent Set</li>\n                        <li>Independent Set → Vertex Cover</li>\n                        <li>Vertex Cover → Hamiltonian Cycle</li>\n                    </ul>\n                `\n            },\n            algorithms: {\n                title: \"Algorithm Comparison\",\n                content: `\n                    <table>\n                        <tr>\n                            <th>Problem Type</th>\n                            <th>Best Known Algorithm</th>\n                            <th>Time Complexity</th>\n                        </tr>\n                        <tr>\n                            <td>Sorting (P)</td>\n                            <td>Merge Sort, QuickSort</td>\n                            <td>O(n log n)</td>\n                        </tr>\n                        <tr>\n                            <td>Shortest Path (P)</td>\n                            <td>Dijkstra's Algorithm</td>\n                            <td>O(E + V log V)</td>\n                        </tr>\n                        <tr>\n                            <td>Traveling Salesman (NP)</td>\n                            <td>Dynamic Programming (Held-Karp)</td>\n                            <td>O(n^2 2^n)</td>\n                        </tr>\n                        <tr>\n                            <td>Boolean SAT (NP)</td>\n                            <td>DPLL Algorithm</td>\n                            <td>O(2^n) in worst case</td>\n                        </tr>\n                    </table>\n                `\n            }\n        };\n        \n        // DOM elements\n        const elements = {\n            showPExamples: document.getElementById('showPExamples'),\n            showNPExamples: document.getElementById('showNPExamples'),\n            showNPComplete: document.getElementById('showNPComplete'),\n            examplesContainer: document.getElementById('examplesContainer'),\n            examplesTitle: document.getElementById('examplesTitle'),\n            examplesList: document.getElementById('examplesList'),\n            \n            problemType: document.getElementById('problemType'),\n            inputSize: document.getElementById('inputSize'),\n            currentSize: document.getElementById('currentSize'),\n            calculateComplexity: document.getElementById('calculateComplexity'),\n            complexityResults: document.getElementById('complexityResults'),\n            resultN: document.getElementById('resultN'),\n            timeComplexity: document.getElementById('timeComplexity'),\n            timeValue: document.getElementById('timeValue'),\n            graphContainer: document.getElementById('graphContainer'),\n            \n            problemSelector: document.getElementById('problemSelector'),\n            problemInputContainer: document.getElementById('problemInputContainer'),\n            solveProblem: document.getElementById('solveProblem'),\n            verifySolution: document.getElementById('verifySolution'),\n            solutionContainer: document.getElementById('solutionContainer'),\n            solutionOutput: document.getElementById('solutionOutput'),\n            verificationResult: document.getElementById('verificationResult'),\n            \n            showImplications: document.getElementById('showImplications'),\n            showCurrentStatus: document.getElementById('showCurrentStatus'),\n            implicationsContent: document.getElementById('implicationsContent'),\n            implicationsList: document.getElementById('implicationsList'),\n            statusText: document.getElementById('statusText'),\n            \n            showReductions: document.getElementById('showReductions'),\n            showAlgorithms: document.getElementById('showAlgorithms'),\n            advancedContent: document.getElementById('advancedContent'),\n            advancedTitle: document.getElementById('advancedTitle'),\n            advancedText: document.getElementById('advancedText')\n        };\n        \n        // Event listeners\n        elements.showPExamples.addEventListener('click', () => showExamples('p', 'P Problems'));\n        elements.showNPExamples.addEventListener('click', () => showExamples('np', 'NP Problems'));\n        elements.showNPComplete.addEventListener('click', () => showExamples('npComplete', 'NP-Complete Problems'));\n        \n        elements.inputSize.addEventListener('input', () => {\n            elements.currentSize.textContent = elements.inputSize.value;\n        });\n        \n        elements.calculateComplexity.addEventListener('click', calculateComplexity);\n        \n        elements.problemSelector.addEventListener('change', updateProblemInput);\n        elements.solveProblem.addEventListener('click', solveCurrentProblem);\n        elements.verifySolution.addEventListener('click', verifyCurrentSolution);\n        \n        elements.showImplications.addEventListener('click', () => showImplications(true));\n        elements.showCurrentStatus.addEventListener('click', () => showImplications(false));\n        \n        elements.showReductions.addEventListener('click', () => showAdvancedContent('reductions'));\n        elements.showAlgorithms.addEventListener('click', () => showAdvancedContent('algorithms'));\n        \n        // Initialize\n        updateProblemInput();\n        \n        // Functions\n        function showExamples(type, title) {\n            elements.examplesTitle.textContent = title;\n            elements.examplesList.innerHTML = '';\n            \n            examples[type].forEach(example => {\n                const li = document.createElement('li');\n                li.textContent = example;\n                elements.examplesList.appendChild(li);\n            });\n            \n            elements.examplesContainer.classList.remove('hidden');\n        }\n        \n        function calculateComplexity() {\n            const type = elements.problemType.value;\n            const n = parseInt(elements.inputSize.value);\n            \n            elements.resultN.textContent = n;\n            \n            let complexityText, value;\n            switch (type) {\n                case 'p':\n                    complexityText = 'n log n';\n                    value = Math.round(n * Math.log2(n));\n                    break;\n                case 'np':\n                    complexityText = '2<sup>n</sup>';\n                    value = Math.round(Math.pow(2, n));\n                    break;\n                case 'exp':\n                    complexityText = 'n<sup>n</sup>';\n                    value = Math.round(Math.pow(n, n));\n                    break;\n            }\n            \n            elements.timeComplexity.innerHTML = complexityText;\n            elements.timeValue.textContent = value.toLocaleString();\n            \n            // Draw simple graph\n            elements.graphContainer.innerHTML = '';\n            const canvas = document.createElement('div');\n            canvas.style.height = '100%';\n            canvas.style.width = '100%';\n            // This would be more sophisticated with actual graphing in a real implementation\n            canvas.innerHTML = `<p>Graph showing growth of ${complexityText} from n=1 to n=${n}</p>`;\n            elements.graphContainer.appendChild(canvas);\n            \n            elements.complexityResults.classList.remove('hidden');\n        }\n        \n        function updateProblemInput() {\n            const problemType = elements.problemSelector.value;\n            const handler = problemHandlers[problemType];\n            const n = parseInt(elements.inputSize.value);\n            \n            elements.problemInputContainer.innerHTML = `\n                <h3>Problem Instance (n=${n})</h3>\n                <div class=\"problem-instance\">${handler.generate(n)}</div>\n            `;\n            \n            elements.solutionContainer.classList.add('hidden');\n            elements.verifySolution.disabled = true;\n        }\n        \n        function solveCurrentProblem() {\n            const problemType = elements.problemSelector.value;\n            const handler = problemHandlers[problemType];\n            const problemInstance = elements.problemInputContainer.querySelector('.problem-instance').textContent;\n            \n            const solution = handler.solve(problemInstance);\n            \n            elements.solutionOutput.innerHTML = `\n                <p><strong>Solution:</strong></p>\n                <div class=\"problem-instance\">${solution}</div>\n            `;\n            \n            elements.verificationResult.innerHTML = '';\n            elements.solutionContainer.classList.remove('hidden');\n            elements.verifySolution.disabled = false;\n            \n            // Store for verification\n            elements.solutionContainer.dataset.problemInstance = problemInstance;\n            elements.solutionContainer.dataset.solution = solution;\n        }\n        \n        function verifyCurrentSolution() {\n            const problemType = elements.problemSelector.value;\n            const handler = problemHandlers[problemType];\n            const problemInstance = elements.solutionContainer.dataset.problemInstance;\n            const solution = elements.solutionContainer.dataset.solution;\n            \n            const isValid = handler.verify(problemInstance, solution);\n            \n            elements.verificationResult.innerHTML = `\n                <p><strong>Verification:</strong> ${isValid ? '✅ Valid solution' : '❌ Invalid solution'}</p>\n            `;\n        }\n        \n        function showImplications(showImplications) {\n            elements.implicationsList.innerHTML = '';\n            elements.statusText.innerHTML = '';\n            \n            if (showImplications) {\n                implications.forEach(item => {\n                    const li = document.createElement('li');\n                    li.textContent = item;\n                    elements.implicationsList.appendChild(li);\n                });\n                elements.implicationsContent.querySelector('h3').textContent = 'If P = NP:';\n            } else {\n                currentStatus.forEach(item => {\n                    const p = document.createElement('p');\n                    p.textContent = item;\n                    elements.statusText.appendChild(p);\n                });\n                elements.implicationsContent.querySelector('h3').textContent = 'Current Status:';\n            }\n            \n            elements.implicationsContent.classList.remove('hidden');\n        }\n        \n        function showAdvancedContent(type) {\n            const content = advancedContent[type];\n            elements.advancedTitle.textContent = content.title;\n            elements.advancedText.innerHTML = content.content;\n            elements.advancedContent.classList.remove('hidden');\n        }\n    </script>\n</body>\n</html>"
